.TH "azure-ephemeral-disk-setup" "8" "June\ 26,\ 2025" "azure-ephemeral-disk-setup @VERSION@" "User Manual"
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
\f[B]azure-ephemeral-disk-setup\f[R] - format and mount Azure ephemeral
NVMe or SCSI disks
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]azure-ephemeral-disk-setup\f[R]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\f[B]azure-ephemeral-disk-setup\f[R] is a one-shot initialization
service for Azure virtual machines that automatically detects,
validates, formats, and mounts ephemeral local disks (NVMe or optionally
SCSI).
It supports multi-disk aggregation with \f[CB]mdadm\f[R] and ensures
safe, idempotent operation.
.PP
This intended to be configured via
\f[CB]/etc/azure-ephemeral-disk-setup.conf\f[R] and used early in the
boot sequence (via \f[CB]systemd\f[R]) to prepare local storage under a
specified mount point, typically \f[CB]/mnt\f[R].
.SH CONFIGURATION VARIABLES
.PP
These may be set in \f[CB]/etc/azure-ephemeral-disk-setup.conf\f[R] or
directly exported into environment (note that any config file would
override the environment):
.TP
\f[CB]AZURE_EPHEMERAL_DISK_SETUP_AGGREGATION\f[R]
\f[CB]mdadm\f[R] (default) or \f[CB]none\f[R].
Defines if multiple NVMe disks are aggregated into RAID-0.
.TP
\f[CB]AZURE_EPHEMERAL_DISK_SETUP_FS_TYPE\f[R]
Filesystem to use: \f[CB]ext4\f[R] (default) or \f[CB]xfs\f[R].
.TP
\f[CB]AZURE_EPHEMERAL_DISK_SETUP_MDADM_CHUNK\f[R]
RAID chunk size, e.g., \f[CB]512K\f[R], \f[CB]1M\f[R].
Default is \f[CB]512K\f[R].
.TP
\f[CB]AZURE_EPHEMERAL_DISK_SETUP_MDADM_NAME\f[R]
RAID name, default: \f[CB]azure-ephemeral-md\f[R].
.TP
\f[CB]AZURE_EPHEMERAL_DISK_SETUP_MOUNT_POINT\f[R]
Mount path, default: \f[CB]/mnt\f[R].
.TP
\f[CB]AZURE_EPHEMERAL_DISK_SETUP_NVME_MODEL_DETECTION\f[R]
If \f[CB]true\f[R], uses NVMe model detection if symlinks are missing.
.TP
\f[CB]AZURE_EPHEMERAL_DISK_SETUP_SCSI_RESOURCE\f[R]
If \f[CB]true\f[R], will fall back to SCSI resource disk if no NVMe disks
are available.
.SH DETAILS
.PP
The service performs the following steps in order:
.IP "1." 3
\f[B]Load Configuration\f[R]:
.RS 4
.IP \[bu] 2
From \f[CB]/etc/azure-ephemeral-disk-setup.conf\f[R] if it exists.
.IP \[bu] 2
There is restrictive filtering to minimize risk of bad configuration:
\f[CB]source <(grep -E \[aq]\[ha]AZURE_EPHEMERAL_DISK_SETUP_[A-Z_]+=[\[dq]\[aq]\[dq]\[aq]\[dq]\[aq]A-Za-z0-9_./:-\[rs] ]+$\[aq] \[dq]${CONFIGURATION_FILE}\[dq])\f[R]
.RE
.IP "2." 3
\f[B]Validate configuration\f[R]:
.RS 4
.IP \[bu] 2
Ensure configuration appears to be valid.
.RE
.IP "3." 3
\f[B]Check Existing Mounts\f[R]:
.RS 4
.IP \[bu] 2
If the mount point is already mounted \f[B]and\f[R] the corresponding
\f[CB]/etc/fstab\f[R] entry includes the comment
\f[CB]comment=azure-ephemeral-disk-setup\f[R], it exits with success.
.IP \[bu] 2
If mounted or defined by another service, it exits with an error.
.RE
.IP "4." 3
\f[B]Disk Detection\f[R]:
.RS 4
.IP \[bu] 2
NVMe disks are discovered via
\f[CB]/dev/disk/azure/local/by-serial/*\f[R].
.RS 2
.IP \[bu] 2
If \f[CB]AZURE_EPHEMERAL_DISK_SETUP_NVME_MODEL_DETECTION=true\f[R]: NVMe
model strings are used to detect disks (to support cases where
azure-vm-utils is not installed).
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
If no NVMe and \f[CB]AZURE_EPHEMERAL_DISK_SETUP_SCSI_RESOURCE=true\f[R],
SCSI resource disk is discovered via \f[CB]/dev/disk/azure/resource\f[R].
.RE
.IP "5." 3
\f[B]Disk Validation\f[R]:
.RS 4
.IP \[bu] 2
NVMe local disks must be:
.RS 2
.IP \[bu] 2
block devices
.IP \[bu] 2
not mounted
.IP \[bu] 2
not partitioned
.IP \[bu] 2
not already formatted
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
SCSI resource disk has an exception for pre-formatted NTFS disks and
must be:
.RS 2
.IP \[bu] 2
empty other than \f[CB]dataloss_warning_readme.txt\f[R] and
\f[CB]System Volume Information\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
not mounted
.IP \[bu] 2
single partition
.RE
.RE
.IP "6." 3
\f[B]Aggregation (if configured)\f[R]:
.RS 4
.IP \[bu] 2
If more than one NVMe local disk is found and
\f[CB]AZURE_EPHEMERAL_DISK_SETUP_AGGREGATION=mdadm\f[R], creates a RAID-0
array with:
.RS 2
.IP \[bu] 2
Metadata version 1.2
.IP \[bu] 2
Chunk size per configuration
.IP \[bu] 2
Name per configuration
.IP \[bu] 2
Exported as \f[CB]/dev/md/<name>_0\f[R]
.RE
.RE
.IP "7." 3
\f[B]Filesystem Formatting\f[R]:
.RS 4
.IP \[bu] 2
Formats the target device with the configured filesystem.
.IP \[bu] 2
Forced formatting is only allowed for SCSI disks with verified NTFS
contents.
.RE
.IP "8." 3
\f[B]Mounting and fstab Update\f[R]:
.RS 4
.IP \[bu] 2
Creates the mount point directory.
.IP \[bu] 2
Old entries with \f[CB]comment=azure-ephemeral-disk-setup\f[R] are
removed.
.IP \[bu] 2
Adds a line to \f[CB]/etc/fstab\f[R] using:
.RS 2
.IP
.nf
\f[CR]
<device> <mount_point> <fs_type> defaults,nofail,comment=azure-ephemeral-disk-setup 0 2
\f[R]
.fi
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
Mounted directly to mount point to support images with read-only fstab.
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.PP
\f[B]0\f[R] \[en] Success
.PD 0
.P
.PD
\f[B]1\f[R] \[en] Configuration or device validation error
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Detect and format ephemeral disks using default settings:
.IP
.nf
\f[CR]
$ sudo azure-ephemeral-disk-setup
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Configure SCSI resource disk fallback:
.IP
.nf
\f[CR]
# /etc/azure-ephemeral-disk-setup.conf
AZURE_EPHEMERAL_DISK_SETUP_SCSI_RESOURCE=true
AZURE_EPHEMERAL_DISK_SETUP_FS_TYPE=ext4
AZURE_EPHEMERAL_DISK_SETUP_MOUNT_POINT=/mnt
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Example fstab entry after setup of SCSI resource disk:
.IP
.nf
\f[CR]
/dev/disk/azure/resource /mnt xfs defaults,nofail,comment=azure-ephemeral-disk-setup 0 2
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Example fstab entry after setup of multiple local NVMe disks:
.IP
.nf
\f[CR]
/dev/md/azure-ephemeral-md_0 /mnt xfs defaults,nofail,comment=azure-ephemeral-disk-setup 0 2
\f[R]
.fi
.SH FILES
.TP
\f[CB]/etc/azure-ephemeral-disk-setup.conf\f[R]
Optional user configuration file.
.TP
\f[CB]/etc/fstab\f[R]
Mount persistence configuration.
.SH DEBUGGING
.PP
The service may be debugged using \f[CB]bash -x\f[R]:
.IP
.nf
\f[CR]
$ sudo bash -x azure-ephemeral-disk-setup
\f[R]
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.PP
\f[B]mdadm(8)\f[R], \f[B]mount(8)\f[R], \f[B]cloud-init(8)\f[R],
\f[B]waagent(8)\f[R]
.PP
Project home: <https://github.com/Azure/azure-vm-utils>
